            <section class="text-content" id="about-us">
              <h3>About Us</h3>
              <p>Gymsight Training isn't a location as much as it is a training philosophy that uses varied, unique and directed methods applied and executed in a way necessary for a given individual's goals, training threshold and attitude. The purpose of our training is to provide efficient, durable, and sustainable results. The training here is hard, unique, and creative, accomplished in a way that instills both confidence and motivation in our clients. In each session, we sweat, we succeed, we fail, we laugh, we expose and then overcome limitations. The most important thing is that we cultivate perseverance, and improvement. We believe that the mind, body, nutrition, and lifestyle factors are intrinsically linked, attributes we focus on molding everyday as we see these as necessary focal points for progression in performance and health. </p>
              <p>
              Here we train in preparation for something, whether it be a sport, work, or life driven objective. The reason for this is that it's easier to train a mind anchored on something tangible than nothing at all. We also create an atmosphere complete with like-minded individuals who enjoy challenging themselves as well as being challenged by others. And while we do set standards so that a certain intensity is maintained, quality in execution is preferred over quantity every time, for every exercise, in every session, and applies to both client and trainer alike. A training session here is a planned event devoid of mirrors, TVs, and similar things that only serve as distractions. What you will find is training equipment and space sufficient for the task, music, inspiration, and milestones.
              </p>
              <p>Gymsight Training is not open to the general public, and walk-ins are strongly discouraged. All individual and group training is conducted under the guidance of a Gymsight trainer, and eligibility is determined through an initial conversation and assessment. If you would like to learn more about training with Gymsight, you are encouraged to explore the website, ask questions, or begin a conversation with a Gymsight Trainer. Click here to ask a question, or here to request a consultation.</p>
            </section>
