                  <h3 class="gymowner-header">Dewayne Hornbeak</h3>
                  <h3 class="header-description">Founder & Training Director</h3>
                  <p>Prior to starting Gymsight Training, Dewayne served honorably in the U.S. Marine Corps as an infantry and special operations team member. After leaving the military in 2003, he began a long career in the international private security field. As a tactical athlete, his long career took him from every part and climate on earth and kept him constantly immersed in physical training as he never knew what area or situation he'd end up in. During this time he also learned that, not only does the gym prepare an individual for a given event or activity, but also closely mirrors various aspects of life (hardship, integrity, courage, adaptation, failure and perseverance).</p>
                  <p>Drawing on cumulative experiences as an athlete, Marine, trainer, and realist, he set out to create a training philosophy and location where dedicated athletes, as well as those willing to work hard to achieve an objective, could train, grow, expose doubts and overcome them, and progress. These are standards that he has continued to maintain and are cornerstone to Gymsight Training.</p>
                  <h4>My take on training:</h4>
                  <p>
                     I understand that there are many different paths for each individual to reach that next level. One thing I've learned in 14+ years as an athlete, coach, team-builder, and educator, is the significance of helping others progress and with that I constantly strive to offer the greatest training to each member I take on. I accomplish this through teaching, succeeding and sometimes falling short, experimentation, listening, personal experience, being restlessly ambitious, leading by example, and by constantly expanding my knowledge base and scope of expertise.
                  </p>
                  <h4>Current goals for my own training:</h4>
                  <p>
                     Currently training for the Bald Eagle Mega Transect taking place in October, and completing another Goruck Challenge event. Rock climbing in the  Northern Cascades. Furthering my own education and continuing to progress in my own strength and conditioning.
                  </p>
                  <h4>Hobbies outside of the gym:</h4>
                  <p>
                     Mountain running, hiking, adventure and travel enthusiast, bad sci-fi movie connoisseur, good beer and vodka, range time, music, reading and researching anything climbing, survival, fitness, and psychology related.
                  </p>
